Vice President Joe Biden issued a statement in response to his chief of staff, Ron Klain, announcing that he will be leaving his post later in January. Biden praised Klain for his 25 years of friendship and advisory, stating that he has done an exceptional job in building his team, implementing his direction on top priorities, and providing valuable counsel. Klain has also played a key role in establishing a strong and positive relationship between Biden's staff and the President's team. Biden expressed pride in their successes over the past two years and wished Klain the best of luck in his future career endeavors.